---
title: Indian-Inspired Eggplant with Tandoori-Spiced Basmati Rice and Cilantro Yogurt Sauce
description: The name tandoori is derived from tandoor, a type of brick and clay oven used throughout India that lends a distinctly smoky taste to everything from veggies and meat to naan bread. In this recipe, we’ve recreated the bold and pungent flavors with the help of a special Tandoori spice blend made with equal parts turmeric, cardamom, paprika, and coriander.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tandoori-spice-eggplant-3f9201c5.jpg
